oracle.adf.view.rich.context

Class ApplicationContextManager.ComponentContextChangeWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.myfaces.trinidad.context.ComponentContextChange
      • oracle.adf.view.rich.context.ApplicationContextChange
        • oracle.adf.view.rich.context.ApplicationContextManager.ComponentContextChangeWrapper
  • Enclosing class:
    ApplicationContextManager

    protected static class ApplicationContextManager.ComponentContextChangeWrapper
extends ApplicationContextChange
    Class to allow a ComponentContextChange to be wrapped as a ApplicationContextChange instance. The implementation simply calls the suspend and resume methods on the wrapped change object that is passed in.

      • suspend

        public void suspend(javax.faces.context.FacesContext context)
        Description copied from class: ApplicationContextChange
        Suspend the context change and revert back to the application context that existed before this context change was originally made.

        It's only valid to suspend a context change that's currently active. The implementation of this method does not need to support a call to suspend a context change that's already suspended.

        Specified by:
        suspend in class ApplicationContextChange
        Parameters:
        context - the FacesContext for the current request.
